        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23627",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wizkid",
                        "name": "wizkid",
                        "displayName": "Emil Hesslow",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I ran into the same problem.\n\nA workaround I found was to do{code}$select = $this->select();\n$select->__toString();\n$select->join('survey_runs', 'survey_runs.id_run = runs.id', array());\n{code}\n\nMy guess is that when calling __toString it seems that the table name is added to $this->_parts[self::FROM] which means that it is now first in the array and everything works.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wizkid",
                        "name": "wizkid",
                        "displayName": "Emil Hesslow",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-23T14:50:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-23T14:50:34.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28261",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "From Christian Grafe\n\nI'd really like to see this bug fixed. If its any help, I think I might \nhave located the cause for this issue:\n\n{code}\n\/\/ If no fields are specified we assume all fields from primary table\nif (!count($fields)) {\n     $this->from($primary, self::SQL_WILDCARD, $schema);\n     $fields = $this->getPart(Zend_Db_Table_Select::COLUMNS);\n}\n{code}\n\nThese lines from Zend_Db_Table_Select::assemble() will add the primary \ntable to our query, only if we have *not* joined another table. I would \nthink that for a Zend_Db_Table_Select query we always want all fields from \nthe primary table. So, imho the above call to $this->from() should be made \nin Zend_Db_Table_Select::__construct(), which fixes the problem for me.\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-16T09:47:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-16T09:47:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31120",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This has been fixed with the solution in ZF-2546, use $table->select(true) to retrieve a select object with the from part pre-loaded.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-18T15:48:32.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-18T15:48:32.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
